fields.description: Indicates the creation date and time for the custom device scope.
fields.name: CreatedDateTime

fields.description: The name of the user experience analytics device Scope configuration.
fields.name: DeviceScopeName

fields.description: Indicates whether a device scope is enabled or disabled. When TRUE, the device scope is enabled. When FALSE, the device scope is disabled. Default value is FALSE.
fields.name: Enabled

fields.description: Indicates whether the device scope configuration is built-in or custom. When TRUE, the device scope configuration is built-in. When FALSE, the device scope configuration is custom. Default value is FALSE.
fields.name: IsBuiltIn

fields.description: Indicates the last updated date and time for the custom device scope.
fields.name: LastModifiedDateTime

fields.description: Device scope configuration query operator. Possible values are: equals, notEquals, contains, notContains, greaterThan, lessThan. Default value: equals.
fields.name: Operator

fields.description: The unique identifier of the person (admin) who created the device scope configuration.
fields.name: OwnerId

fields.description: Device scope configuration parameter. It will be expend in future to add more parameter. Eg: device scope parameter can be OS version, Disk Type, Device manufacturer, device model or Scope tag. Default value: scopeTag.
fields.name: Parameter

fields.description: Indicates the device scope status after the device scope has been enabled. Possible values are: none, computing, insufficientData or completed. Default value is none.
fields.name: Status

fields.description: The device scope configuration query clause value.
fields.name: Value

fields.description: The unique identifier for a user device scope tag Id used for the creation of device scope configuration.
fields.name: ValueObjectId
